    "causal_summary": "Three retrieval quality features — session boost, causal boost, and deep query expansion — are each gated behind explicit opt-in environment variables (`SPECKIT_SESSION_BOOST`, `SPECKIT_CAUSAL_BOOST`). Because `isFeatureEnabled()` in `rollout-policy.ts` treats an *undefined* env var as ON, but `session-boost.ts` and `causal-boost.ts` call `isFeatureEnabled` with their specific flag names that users typically do not set, the net effect is that the features are effectively OFF for all default installations. A test search for \"semantic search\" confirmed: `sessionBoostApplied: \"off\"`, `causalBoostApplied: \"off\"`, and `deepExpansion: false` even in `deep` mode.",
